content: Well, I liked your original definition of supernatural from before, but I am ok if you would like to revise it, "Broadly speaking, the term "supernatural" refers to phenomena or entities that are believed to exist beyond the scope of natural laws or the physical world, and are typically attributed to some sort of higher power, deity, or divine force. This can include concepts such as gods, angels, demons, spirits, and other supernatural beings or forces that are often associated with religious or spiritual belief systems." Let me know if there is anything you would like to change.
